line_1: Wisdom unclogg'd by years, with toil unbought,
line_2: A zeal by vigour kindled, rul'd by thought.

line_1: Domes with gold and toil unbought,
line_2: Rise by magick pow'r of thought,
No — all that's worth a wish, a thought,

line_1: And spotless senates here remain unbought.
line_2: So distant regions shall employ their thought,
